node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Charlie Puth on July 29, 2021 tagging @justinbieber, @blakeslatkin, @cashmerecat, @omerfedi, and @thekidlaroi. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text: I don’t usually make posts like this, but this was too special to pass up. We all weren’t even planning on doing a session that day, I just needed to get out of the house. Laroi pointed to the Juno and said “just play something.” I hit setting one in bank 1 and started playing the line you hear now, not thinking much of it. Laroi then grabs the mic and FREESTYLES the chorus you hear now, but sings it melodically parallel to the synth melody. WOW. So so clever. My mouth hit the ground… I was so impressed. We all did the scratch in under an hour and now I’m being told it’s the biggest song in the world. That’s pretty sweet- thank you for having me be a part of this. And thank you Justin for adding such value and depth to the record. Your voice is insane …..damn why can’t I stop listening to this?
